sentences: Donald Edgar "Gus" Backus (September 12, 1937 – February 21, 2019) was an American singer and actor.

After he was stationed as an Airman in the U.S. Air Force at Wiesbaden Air Base in 1957, Backus had to leave The Del-Vikings and started singing Schlager music in 1960s West Germany.
19 of his songs between 1960 and 1967 made the charts, including eight Top Ten hits.
He landed a Number 1 hit in the German charts with his song "Der Mann im Mond" ("The Man in the Moon") in 1961.
In addition to singing, Backus also appeared in nearly 30 film and television productions between 1959 and 1970, often showcasing his songs.
Backus came back to America for some years in the 1970s and worked as a foreman on oil fields in Texas, later returning to Germany.
